Private equity firm  Bain Capital  and
the Government of Singapore Investment Corp. (GIC) will buy 30
percent of Hero Investment Pvt. Ltd., which owns 17 percent of  Hero Honda Motors Ltd ., for 39 billion rupees, the Economic
Times reported, without saying where it got the information.  The deal would give Bain and GIC an indirect holding of
close to 13 percent in Hero Honda, according to the report.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
